      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Legally, the situation is complex, with several competing claims, notably involving China's extensive \"nine-dash line\" versus the arguments presented by various other claimant states under international law. The primary framework is the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea (UNCLOS), which helps define maritime zones like Exclusive Economic Zones (EEZs). However, nations often interpret and apply this convention differently, making a single, universally agreed-upon \"legitimate\" right elusive right now.",
      "source": "target",
